					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">On the 6502, the branch/jump sequence is usually used when a branch would fall out of the +127/-128 range.<br /><br />This is logically equivalent to :<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">nmi:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;pha<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;txa<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;pha<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;tya<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;pha<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda &lt;VRAM_UPDATE<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;beq @skipUpd<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;;never gets here<br />@skipUpd:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;;always gets here</div><br /><br />So this simply means your variable VRAM_UPDATE is always #0.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

