				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">There are different ways to do it, but yes that is <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=10&amp;t=11151" class="postlink">how I would recommend</a> doing it.<br /><br />1. Put all your intended updates to VRAM in some RAM buffer. Probably you have a 256 byte page for the OAM update, but also you will likely need RAM buffers for palette and nametable changes.<br />2. Set a flag variable that tells the next NMI that you are finished filling the buffers and need this data posted to the screen.<br />3. Wait for NMI. Make a loop that waits for the flag variable to be 0 again.<br />4. NMI checks the flag, and updates the PPU data copying from those buffers during vblank.<br />5. NMI sets the flag to false, and returns.<br />6. Your wait loop exits now that the flag is 0. The buffers are now free to fill with new data.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
