				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Rainwarrior is right. I just wanted to add that the sprite display list MUST be 256 bytes long and MUST start on the first byte of a 256-byte page of RAM. For example, it cannot start at $0240 and end at $033F because those are two different pages ($02 and $03). Unused sprites' Y coordinates should be $F0 or greater. <br /><br />Typically I put palette, nametable, and CHR RAM updates in $0100-$019F (the part of the stack page that the program doesn't otherwise use) and put the display list to be copied to OAM at $0200-$02FF. This leaves $0000-$00FF (the zero page) and $0300-$07FF for other uses.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
